The paper deals with geometric optimization problems involving points in high-dimensional spaces, which suggests that it belongs to the computational geometry (cs.CG) sub-category. The use of upper and lower bounds, approximation algorithms, and the fact that the problem is NP-hard also suggest that it could belong to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), numerical analysis (cs.NA), and computational complexity (cs.CC).
